<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="130" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-06"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1592.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch, No. 2916, of the 20th of April last, reporting that through an
                            error in a telegram to you from our consul-general at Shanghai you were
                            led to demand <pb facs="0294" n="198" xml:id="pg_198"/> 500 taels
                            instead of 5,000 taels from the Chinese Government as indemnity for
                            iujuries to Americans, resulting from the riot at Chiang Pei. You add
                            that you have informed the Yamên of the mistake and have demanded the
                            latter sum.</p>
                        <p>Such mistakes suggest that, in telegraphing important sums, words and not
                            figures should be employed.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>